@page "/privacy"
@using MudBlazor

<MudContainer>
    <MudPaper Class="pa-4">
        <MudTypography Variant="H4">Privacy Policy</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography Variant="Subtitle1"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> [Insert Date]</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">1. Introduction</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>Welcome to LoanMyTools.com ("we," "our," "us"). Your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our website and services.</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">2. Information We Collect</MudTypography>
        <MudList T="string">
            <MudListItem><strong>Contact Information:</strong> Your name, email address, and phone number.</MudListItem>
            <MudListItem><strong>Account Information:</strong> Information required to create and manage your account.</MudListItem>
            <MudListItem><strong>Transaction Information:</strong> Details about the tools you lend, borrow, or request through our platform.</MudListItem>
            <MudListItem><strong>Usage Information:</strong> Data on how you interact with our website, including log files and cookies.</MudListItem>
        </MudList>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">3. How We Use Your Information</MudTypography>
        <MudList T="string">
            <MudListItem>Comply with legal obligations.</MudListItem>
        </MudList>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">4. Data Sharing and Third Parties</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes. Your information is only accessible by LoanMyTools.com for the purpose of operating the platform.</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">5. Payment Processing and Data Security</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>Donations are handled securely through PayPal, and we do not store or process any credit card data. LoanMyTools.com does not collect, store, or have access to any PCI-sensitive payment information.</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>We implement reasonable security measures to protect your personal information. However, no online service is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">6. Your Choices and Rights</MudTypography>
        <MudList T="string">
            <MudListItem>You may update or delete your account information by accessing your profile settings.</MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>You may opt out of non-essential communications at any time.</MudListItem>
            <MudListItem>If you have questions about your data, you can contact us at [Insert Contact Email].</MudListItem>
        </MudList>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">7. Retention of Data</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>We retain your information as long as necessary to provide our services and comply with legal obligations. If you delete your account, we may retain some information for record-keeping purposes.</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated effective date. Continued use of our services constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.</MudTypography>
        
        <MudTypography Variant="H5">9. Contact Us</MudTypography>
        <MudTypography>If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [Insert Contact Email].</MudTypography>
    </MudPaper>
</MudContainer>



